This paper deals with frequent itemset mining, which is a common task in data mining and database systems. The focus is on mining itemsets from streaming data, which falls under the category of data stream management systems (DSMS) and online analytical processing (OLAP). Therefore, cs.DB and cs.DS are the most likely categories. The paper also proposes a novel algorithm that uses approximation techniques to handle resource constraints, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. Hence, cs.LG and cs.AI are also likely categories. Finally, the paper discusses the performance of the proposed algorithm in terms of precision and recall, which are evaluation metrics commonly used in information retrieval (IR). Therefore, cs.IR is also a possible category.
